</span><span class='line'>  <span class="kd">public</span> <span class="kt">void</span> <span class="nf">invoke</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="n">Promise</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">lt</span><span class="o">;</span><span class="n">String</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">gt</span><span class="o">;</span> <span class="n">promise</span><span class="o">)</span> <span class="o">{</span>
</span><span class='line'>     <span class="k">try</span> <span class="o">{</span>
</span><span class='line'>        <span class="n">assertThat</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="n">promise</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="na">get</span><span class="o">(),</span> <span class="n">is</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="s">&quot;Foobar&quot;</span><span class="o">));</span>
</span><span class='line'>     <span class="o">}</span> <span class="k">catch</span> <span class="o">(</span><span class="n">Exception</span> <span class="n">e</span><span class="o">)</span> <span class="o">{}</span>
</span><span class='line'>     <span class="k">throw</span> <span class="k">new</span> <span class="nf">RuntimeException</span><span class="o">();</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="o">}</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">&lt;/</span><span class="n">code</span><span class="o">&gt;&lt;/</span><span class="n">pre</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">p</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>   <span class="o">});</span>
</span><span class='line'>   <span class="n">promise</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="na">get</span><span class="o">();</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">}&lt;/</span><span class="n">p</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">p</span><span class="o">&gt;</span><span class="nd">@Test</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="kd">public</span> <span class="kt">void</span> <span class="nf">test_promise_with_all</span><span class="o">()</span> <span class="kd">throws</span> <span class="n">Exception</span> <span class="o">{</span>
</span><span class='line'>   <span class="n">Promise</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">String</span><span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="n">fooPromise</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="k">new</span> <span class="n">Promise</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">String</span><span class="o">&gt;();</span>
</span><span class='line'>   <span class="n">fooPromise</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="na">invoke</span><span class="o">(&amp;</span><span class="n">ldquo</span><span class="o">;</span><span class="n">Foo</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rdquo</span><span class="o">;);</span>
</span><span class='line'>   <span class="n">Promise</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">String</span><span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="n">barPromise</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="k">new</span> <span class="n">Promise</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">String</span><span class="o">&gt;();</span>
</span><span class='line'>   <span class="n">barPromise</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="na">invoke</span><span class="o">(&amp;</span><span class="n">ldquo</span><span class="o">;</span><span class="n">Bar</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rdquo</span><span class="o">;);</span>
</span><span class='line'>   <span class="n">Promise</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">lt</span><span class="o">;</span><span class="n">Tuple</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">lt</span><span class="o">;</span><span class="n">String</span><span class="o">,</span> <span class="n">String</span><span class="o">&gt;&gt;</span> <span class="n">foobarPromise</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">Promise</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="na">wait2</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="n">fooPromise</span><span class="o">,</span> <span class="n">barPromise</span><span class="o">);</span>
</span><span class='line'>   <span class="n">Tuple</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">lt</span><span class="o">;</span><span class="n">String</span><span class="o">,</span> <span class="n">String</span><span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="n">tuple</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">foobarPromise</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="na">get</span><span class="o">();</span>
</span><span class='line'>   <span class="n">assertThat</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="n">tuple</span><span class="o">.&lt;</span><span class="n">em</span><span class="o">&gt;</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="o">,</span> <span class="n">is</span><span class="o">(&amp;</span><span class="n">ldquo</span><span class="o">;</span><span class="n">Foo</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rdquo</span><span class="o">;));</span>
</span><span class='line'>   <span class="n">assertThat</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="n">tuple</span><span class="o">.&lt;/</span><span class="n">em</span><span class="o">&gt;</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="o">,</span> <span class="n">is</span><span class="o">(&amp;</span><span class="n">ldquo</span><span class="o">;</span><span class="n">Bar</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rdquo</span><span class="o">;));</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">}</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<h3>Pattern Matching</h3>


<p>Le <a href="http://www.playframework.org/documentation/1.2/libs#PatternMatching" target="_blank">Pattern Matching</a> <em>&agrave; la Java</em> est venu par le travail sur les Web Sockets. L'id&eacute;e est, comme dans le dernier exemple de ce <a href="http://www.playframework.org/documentation/1.2/asynchronous#UsingWebSockets" target="_blank">paragraphe</a>, d'&eacute;viter les nombreux tests et casts qui polluent la lecture du code <em>(le m&eacute;tier ne ressort pas)</em>. Par un petit <em>hack </em>sur la boucle <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">for </span>et en passant par des objets <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">Matchers</span>, il est possible de simuler un comportement de Pattern Matching. Exemple :</p>


<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'> <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='java'><span class='line'><span class="nd">@Test</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="kd">public</span> <span class="kt">void</span> <span class="nf">test_matcher_object</span><span class="o">()</span> <span class="o">{</span>
</span><span class='line'>   <span class="n">String</span> <span class="n">value</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">ldquo</span><span class="o">;</span><span class="n">Foobar</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rdquo</span><span class="o">;;</span>
</span><span class='line'>   <span class="k">for</span> <span class="o">(</span><span class="n">String</span> <span class="n">s</span> <span class="o">:</span> <span class="n">String</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="na">and</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="n">StartsWith</span><span class="o">(&amp;</span><span class="n">ldquo</span><span class="o">;</span><span class="n">Foo</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rdquo</span><span class="o">;)).</span><span class="na">match</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="n">value</span><span class="o">))</span> <span class="o">{&lt;/</span><span class="n">p</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">pre</span><span class="o">&gt;&lt;</span><span class="n">code</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>  <span class="n">value</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">s</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="na">toUpperCase</span><span class="o">();</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">&lt;/</span><span class="n">code</span><span class="o">&gt;&lt;/</span><span class="n">pre</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">p</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>   <span class="o">}</span>
</span><span class='line'>   <span class="n">assertThat</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="n">value</span><span class="o">,</span> <span class="n">is</span><span class="o">(&amp;</span><span class="n">ldquo</span><span class="o">;</span><span class="n">FOOBAR</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rdquo</span><span class="o">;));</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">}</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p>Ces <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">Matchers </span>sont pour l'instant peu nombreux mais ils devraient tr&egrave;s rapidement voir leur nombre grossir. J'attends impatiemment le <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">Matcher </span>sur les options <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">Some </span>et&nbsp;<span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">None </span><img title="Tongue out" src="http://www.web-tambouille.fr/tinymce/plugins/emoticons/img/smiley-tongue-out.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" />.</p>


<h3>Conclusion</h3>


<p>Cette librairie est donc tr&egrave;s utile. On voit que la partie <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">Promise </span>a &eacute;t&eacute; tr&egrave;s travaill&eacute;e car utilis&eacute;e pour l'impl&eacute;mentation des Web Sockets que beaucoup attendaient.</p>


<p>Tout ce qui est <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">Eithers&nbsp;</span>et <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">Tuples</span> est d'ores et d&eacute;j&agrave; exploitable. Un petit b&eacute;mol pour  l'<span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">Option</span>&nbsp;et le Pattern Matching qui m&eacute;riteraient d'&ecirc;tre &eacute;toff&eacute;s. Peut-&ecirc;tre pour Play 1.3 ou Play 2.0 !</p>

]]></content>
    </entry>
    
