<h3>Utilisation</h3>


<p>Comme je l'ai dit, rien de mieux de les tests pour voir comment tout fonctionne. Donc apr&egrave;s un petit <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">git clone</span> et un import maven dans mon <a href="http://www.jetbrains.com/idea/" target="_blank">IDE pr&eacute;f&eacute;r&eacute;</a>, me voici en train de me balader dans le code de la librairie. Une bonne documentation Javadoc ainsi que des tests pour chaque Funky classe.</p>


<h4>Runnable</h4>


<p>Commen&ccedil;ons par le Runnable Java, voici comment nous allons l'&eacute;crire et l'ex&eacute;cuter avec FunkyJFunctional :</p>


<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'> <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='java'><span class='line'><span class="kd">class</span> <span class="nc">Increment</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="n">Runnable</span> <span class="n">runnable</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">FunkyJava</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="na">withRun</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="n">Increment</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="na">class</span><span class="o">);&lt;/</span><span class="n">p</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">p</span><span class="o">&gt;</span><span class="n">assertEquals</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="o">,</span> <span class="n">counter</span><span class="o">);</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="n">runnable</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="na">run</span><span class="o">();</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="n">assertEquals</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="o">,</span> <span class="n">counter</span><span class="o">);</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p>Nous avons donc, et nous allons en prendre l'habitude, &agrave; cr&eacute;er une classe qui contiendra notre code m&eacute;tier.</p>


<p>Cette classe sera ensuite donn&eacute;e &agrave; la classe <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">FunkyJava</span> et plus particuli&egrave;rement &agrave; la m&eacute;thode <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">withRun</span> qui s'occupera pour nous de la transformation de notre classe en un <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">Runnable</span> ex&eacute;cutable. Sur le papier, cette m&eacute;thode nous renvoit un objet <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">ClassRunnable</span>&nbsp;<em>(qui impl&eacute;mente <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">Runnable</span>)</em> qui joue un r&ocirc;le de proxy pour cr&eacute;er l'objet et g&eacute;rer ses param&egrave;tres.</p>


<p>Il y a plusieurs m&eacute;thodes disponibles <em>(avec ou sans param&egrave;tre, <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">withCall</span>...)</em>. En utilisant un import statique, comme on sait que les m&eacute;thodes&nbsp;<span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">withXXX&nbsp;</span>viendront toutes de FunkyJFunctional, nous obtenons :</p>


<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'> <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='java'><span class='line'><span class="kd">class</span> <span class="nc">Increment</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="n">Runnable</span> <span class="n">runnable</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">withRun</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="n">Increment</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="na">class</span><span class="o">);&lt;/</span><span class="n">p</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">p</span><span class="o">&gt;</span><span class="n">assertEquals</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="o">,</span> <span class="n">counter</span><span class="o">);</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="n">runnable</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="na">run</span><span class="o">();</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="n">assertEquals</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="o">,</span> <span class="n">counter</span><span class="o">);</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<h4>Comparator</h4>


<p>Autre exemple avec un <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">Comparator</span> Java, il fonctionne de la m&ecirc;me mani&egrave;re avec la m&eacute;thode <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">withComp</span> qui nous vient aussi de FunkyJava :</p>


<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'> <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='java'><span class='line'><span class="n">List</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">Person</span><span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="n">persons</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">asList</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="k">new</span> <span class="n">Person</span><span class="o">(&amp;</span><span class="n">ldquo</span><span class="o">;</span><span class="n">John</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rdquo</span><span class="o">;),</span> <span class="k">new</span> <span class="n">Person</span><span class="o">(&amp;</span><span class="n">ldquo</span><span class="o">;</span><span class="n">Joe</span><span class="o">&amp;</span><span class="n">rdquo</span><span class="o">;));&lt;</span><span class="n">br</span> <span class="o">/&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="kd">class</span> <span class="nc">Sort</span> <span class="kd">extends</span> <span class="n">Comp</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">Person</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="n">Collections</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="na">sort</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="n">persons</span><span class="o">,</span> <span class="n">withComp</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="n">Sort</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="na">class</span><span class="o">));&lt;/</span><span class="n">p</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">p</span><span class="o">&gt;</span><span class="n">assertEquals</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="n">asList</span><span class="o">(</span><span class="n">joe</span><span class="o">,</span> <span class="n">john</span><span class="o">),</span> <span class="n">persons</span><span class="o">);</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p>On remarque ici que comme comparator prend 2 objets en param&egrave;tres pour les comparer, nous n'avons pas un param&egrave;tre <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">t</span> &agrave; disposition mais un param&egrave;tre <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">t1</span> et un param&egrave;tre <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">t2</span>. Et de m&ecirc;me, <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">withComp</span> nous renverra un objet <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">ClassComparator</span> qui s'occupera de comparer les donn&eacute;es pendant l'ex&eacute;cution du <span style="font-family: 'courier new', courier;">sort</span> &agrave; partir du code dans le bloc.</p>


